Now I have a complete picture. Here is the full documentation of all share/export patterns in the codebase.

---

## Pattern Examples: Share / Export / Social Media in the Lenses Codebase

### Pattern 1: Screenshot to Clipboard + Twitter Intent (dom-to-image)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/data/ScreenShot.js:1-123`

This is the core screenshot utility. It uses the `dom-to-image` library to capture a DOM element as a PNG blob, copies it to the clipboard, and falls back to downloading the image if clipboard is unsupported.

```javascript
import domtoimage from 'dom-to-image';

export function takeScreenshot(widgetContainerRef, showToast) {
  const element = widgetContainerRef.current || 
                 (typeof widgetContainerRef === 'object' && widgetContainerRef.nodeType ? widgetContainerRef : null);

  if (!element) {
    console.error('Invalid reference provided to takeScreenshot');
    if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
      showToast("Failed to capture screenshot: Invalid element reference");
    }
    return;
  }

  domtoimage.toBlob(element, {
    quality: 1.0,
    bgcolor: 'transparent',
    style: {
      'transform': 'none',
      'transform-origin': 'none'
    }
  })
  .then(function (blob) {
    if (navigator.clipboard && window.ClipboardItem) {
      try {
        const item = new ClipboardItem({'image/png': blob});
        navigator.clipboard.write([item])
          .then(() => {
            if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
              showToast("Screenshot copied to clipboard!");
            }
          })
          .catch(error => {
            console.error('Error copying to clipboard:', error);
            downloadFromBlob(blob);
            if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
              showToast("Clipboard not supported, image downloaded instead.");
            }
          });
      } catch (error) {
        console.error('Error with clipboard:', error);
        downloadFromBlob(blob);
        if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
          showToast("Clipboard error, image downloaded instead.");
        }
      }
    } else {
      downloadFromBlob(blob);
      if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
        showToast("Clipboard not supported, image downloaded instead.");
      }
    }
  })
  .catch(function (error) {
    console.error('Screenshot error:', error);
    if (typeof showToast === 'function') {
      showToast("Failed to capture screenshot. Check console for details.");
    }
  });
}

function downloadFromBlob(blob) {
  const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  const a = document.createElement('a');
  a.style.display = 'none';
  a.href = url;
  a.download = `screenshot_${new Date().toISOString()}.png`;
  document.body.appendChild(a);
  a.click();
  setTimeout(() => {
    document.body.removeChild(a);
    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
  }, 100);
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Library: `dom-to-image` (`^2.6.0`) declared in `apps/lenses/package.json:32`
- Captures a DOM element via `domtoimage.toBlob()`
- Primary path: copy PNG to clipboard via `ClipboardItem` API
- Fallback path: download as `.png` file via dynamic `<a>` element
- Additional unused helpers: `blobToDataURL`, `downloadImage`, `copyToClipboardModern`
- Safari is excluded from the screenshot/tweet flow (checked via `isSafari` context)

---

### Pattern 2: Twitter/X "Tweet it!" Button in Widget Navbar (Desktop)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/widget_modules/interaction/elements/WidgetNavbar.jsx:1-132`

Each chart widget has a navbar with a Twitter icon button. Pressing it triggers the screenshot flow (copies to clipboard, then opens Twitter intent).

```jsx
import { File, Twitter, Table, BarChart2} from 'react-feather';

function WidgetNavbar({ type, exportEnabled, onExportClick, onSettingsClick,
  onScreenshotClick, settingsEnabled, showTable, setShowTable,
  widgetContainerRef, showToast, infoPopupId, widgetType, title,
  interactionElements }) {

  const { isSafari, windowWidth } = useContext(AppContext)

  const handleScreenshotClick = () => {
    onScreenshotClick(widgetContainerRef, showToast);
  };

  const navIcons = () => {
    let navIcons = [
      // ... table toggle button, export CSV button ...
      !isSafari && (
        <Tooltip content="Tweet it!" color="default" key="twitter-tooltip">
          <Button
            key="twitter-button"
            className="icon-button"
            size="sm"
            isIconOnly
            onPress={handleScreenshotClick}
            variant="light"
          ><Twitter width="14px" /></Button>
        </Tooltip>)
    ];
    return navIcons
  }

  // Collapses to dropdown on mobile (windowWidth < 768)
  let collapse = windowWidth < 768 ? true : false
  if (collapse) {
    menu = <NavbarCollapsed onScreenshotClick={handleScreenshotClick} ... />
  } else {
    menu = navIcons()
  }

  return (
    <div className='widget-menu'>{menu}</div>
  );
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `react-feather` `Twitter` icon
- Conditionally hidden on Safari (`!isSafari`)
- On desktop (>= 768px): renders as a standalone icon button with tooltip "Tweet it!"
- On mobile (< 768px): collapses into the `NavbarCollapsed` dropdown menu

---

### Pattern 3: Twitter/X Share in Collapsed Widget Navbar (Mobile)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/widget_modules/interaction/elements/WidgetNavbarCollapsed.jsx:1-75`

On mobile, the same screenshot/tweet action appears as a dropdown item.

```jsx
import { File, MoreHorizontal, Twitter, Settings, BarChart2, Table } from "react-feather";

function NavbarCollapsed({ onSettingsClick, onExportClick, onScreenshotClick, showTable, toggleTableView, exportEnabled, widgetType }) {
  const { isSafari } = useContext(AppContext)

  return (
    <Dropdown>
      <DropdownTrigger>
        <Button isIconOnly size="sm" variant="light" className="text-foreground">
          <MoreHorizontal width="18px" />
        </Button>
      </DropdownTrigger>
      <DropdownMenu variant="faded" aria-label="Dropdown menu with description">
        {/* ... toggle table/chart ... */}
        {!isSafari && (
          <DropdownItem
            description="Share a screenshot on X"
            startContent={<Twitter width={16} />}
            className="gap-4"
            onPress={handleScreenshotClick}
            key="twitter"
          >
            Tweet it!
          </DropdownItem>
        )}
        <DropdownItem
          className="gap-4"
          onPress={handleExportClick}
          disabled={exportEnabled ? false : true}
          key="export"
          description="Export data to a CSV file"
          startContent={<File width={16} />}>
          Export CSV
        </DropdownItem>
      </DropdownMenu>
    </Dropdown>
  );
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `@heroui/react` `Dropdown` / `DropdownMenu` / `DropdownItem`
- Description text: "Share a screenshot on X"
- Same Safari exclusion pattern

---

### Pattern 4: Toast + Twitter Intent After Screenshot

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/general_modules/Toast.jsx:1-44`

After a screenshot is copied to clipboard, a toast appears that opens a Twitter intent URL when clicked.

```jsx
const tweetFunction = (widgetTitle, toastCloser) => {
    window.open(`https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=${encodeURIComponent(
      `A screenshot of the ${widgetTitle} widget of Lenses has been copied to your clipboard. Just paste it here! @NumiaData @DataLenses`
    )}`);
}

function ToastMsg({ closeToast, toastProps, type, widgetTitle }) {
    if (type === "clipboard") {
        return (
            <div className='toast-container' onClick={tweetFunction(widgetTitle)}>
                <Check width={40} stroke={`${colors.gain})`} />
                <div className='toast-text-block'>
                  <p> Thanks for sharing some alpha with the Interchain community!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        )
    }
    return (
        <div className='toast-container'>
            <Check fill="none" stroke={`${colors.gain})`} />
        </div>
    )
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `window.open()` with `https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=...`
- Pre-fills tweet text mentioning `@NumiaData` and `@DataLenses`
- Instructs users to paste the clipboard screenshot into the tweet
- The toast in the Widget itself uses a different, simpler pattern via `addToast` from `@heroui/react` (see Widget.jsx line 193-199)

