### Pattern 6: CSV Export via Modal (react-csv)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/widget_modules/interaction/ExportModal.jsx:1-441`

A modal-based CSV export that lets users customize date range, timezone, and time aggregation before downloading.

```jsx
import { CSVLink } from "react-csv";

// Hidden CSVLink triggered programmatically:
{dataState === "valid" && (
  <CSVLink
    data={parseDataForCSV(aggregatedData)}
    filename={`${title}_Data_${
      filterKey ? `id-${filterKey}` : "all"
    }_${dateRange.start}_${dateRange.end}${unit === "dollar" ? "_USD" : ""}.csv`}
    ref={csvLinkRef}
    target="_blank"
    style={{ display: "none" }}
  />
)}

// Triggered by button click:
const rightButtonAction = useCallback(() => {
  if (dataState === "valid" && aggregatedData && csvLinkRef.current) {
    csvLinkRef.current.link.click();
    setTimeout(() => { closeHandler(); }, 500);
  } else if (dataState === "idle" || dataState === "error") {
    setIsManualLoading(true);
    setShouldFetch(false);
    setShouldFetch(true);
  }
}, [dataState, aggregatedData, closeHandler]);
```

**Key aspects**:
- Library: `react-csv` (`^2.2.2`) declared in `apps/lenses/package.json:45`
- Two-step flow: first "Fetch Data", then "Download CSV"
- Gated behind Clerk authentication (shows `Paywall` if not signed in)
- Customizable date range, timezone picker, time frame switch, and unit toggle
- Hidden `<CSVLink>` is clicked programmatically via ref

