### Pattern 2: Twitter/X "Tweet it!" Button in Widget Navbar (Desktop)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/widget_modules/interaction/elements/WidgetNavbar.jsx:1-132`

Each chart widget has a navbar with a Twitter icon button. Pressing it triggers the screenshot flow (copies to clipboard, then opens Twitter intent).

```jsx
import { File, Twitter, Table, BarChart2} from 'react-feather';

function WidgetNavbar({ type, exportEnabled, onExportClick, onSettingsClick,
  onScreenshotClick, settingsEnabled, showTable, setShowTable,
  widgetContainerRef, showToast, infoPopupId, widgetType, title,
  interactionElements }) {

  const { isSafari, windowWidth } = useContext(AppContext)

  const handleScreenshotClick = () => {
    onScreenshotClick(widgetContainerRef, showToast);
  };

  const navIcons = () => {
    let navIcons = [
      // ... table toggle button, export CSV button ...
      !isSafari && (
        <Tooltip content="Tweet it!" color="default" key="twitter-tooltip">
          <Button
            key="twitter-button"
            className="icon-button"
            size="sm"
            isIconOnly
            onPress={handleScreenshotClick}
            variant="light"
          ><Twitter width="14px" /></Button>
        </Tooltip>)
    ];
    return navIcons
  }

  // Collapses to dropdown on mobile (windowWidth < 768)
  let collapse = windowWidth < 768 ? true : false
  if (collapse) {
    menu = <NavbarCollapsed onScreenshotClick={handleScreenshotClick} ... />
  } else {
    menu = navIcons()
  }

  return (
    <div className='widget-menu'>{menu}</div>
  );
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `react-feather` `Twitter` icon
- Conditionally hidden on Safari (`!isSafari`)
- On desktop (>= 768px): renders as a standalone icon button with tooltip "Tweet it!"
- On mobile (< 768px): collapses into the `NavbarCollapsed` dropdown menu

