### Pattern 7: URL Share Button (SavingsCalculator)

**Found in**: `/Users/alvaro/Workspace/numia/lenses/apps/lenses/components/apps/SavingsCalculator.jsx:334-371, 620-668`

A different sharing pattern: generates a shareable URL with query parameters and copies it to clipboard.

```jsx
import { Copy, Share2 } from "react-feather";

// URL construction:
const shareURL = useMemo(() => {
  const baseURL = "https://datalenses.zone/chain/celestia/calculator";
  let shareURLString = baseURL;
  if (comparisonType === "rollup") {
    shareURLString = `${baseURL}?tab=${comparisonType}&stack=${selectedLayer2}`;
  }
  if (comparisonType === "layer") {
    shareURLString = `${baseURL}?tab=${comparisonType}&layer=${selectedLayer}`;
  }
  if (use4844Costs) {
    shareURLString += "&eip=true";
  }
  return shareURLString;
}, [comparisonType, use4844Costs, selectedLayer2, selectedLayer]);

// Copy handler:
const handleURLCopy = () => {
  navigator.clipboard.writeText(shareURL);
  setCopied(true);
  setTimeout(() => {
    setCopied(false);
    setIsOpen(false);
  }, 800);
};

// UI: Popover with Share2 icon trigger
<Button isIconOnly className="bg-background" onPress={() => setIsOpen(true)}>
  <Share2 width={16} />
</Button>
// Inside popover: shows the URL and a copy button
```

**Key aspects**:
- Uses `react-feather` `Share2` and `Copy` icons
- Builds a shareable URL with current state encoded as query parameters
- Uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` for copying text
- Shows a Popover with the URL and a copy button
- Visual feedback: text changes to "Copied!" briefly

